<br>
However, if you see Burnout IV for less than 500pp, then get it. If you're still casting SPELL Burnout III, not using Quest legs, then there's no harm in casting Burnout 4 instead.<br>
<br>
At levcel 56, one the few spells I am missing is Burnout IV,. and I'm in no hurry to get it. In the meantime I have managed to save up for a ghetto horse and a burnt wood staff: a bit pricy at 9.5K, but better that than more! With this equipment I am grinding away to 57 on Seafuries (none green yet, but even 49 Fire is now Lite Blue!) faster than I was before. I'd rather this than a spell I can't use yet.<br>
<br>
ONLY buy spells if you see them for a BARGAIN price (As for BOV, that's 2K or under) or if they're within two levels of your own.<br>
<br>
Also, I've seen quite a few Burnout IVs for sale around the Bazaar for as much as 5K! Lord onyl knows why! I make it my personal mission to tell the merchats how stupid theya re for putting the price up THAT high! As if ANY Mage is gonna mistake THAT for Burnout V! HAH! Have fun cooling your heels in the bazaar, ya lewt whores! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
